{
  "texts": [
    "States: Motivation and OverviewMotivated by the above discussion, our next step is to investigate the ground states of the strained BM model.",
    "Unsurprisingly, given the focus of this review, our tool of choice for doing so will be HF mean-field theory.",
    "The rationale behind this choice is as follows.",
    "Recall that the strong-coupling picture introduced in the preceding section builds on the fact that in the chiral-flat limit, the exact ground state is a Slater determinant.",
    "Due to the enormous U (4) × U (4) symmetry of this limit, there are many degenerate choices, but on perturbing away by adding nonzero w AA and reinstating the singleparticle dispersion, specific Slater determinants are selected at each integer filling."
  ]
}